context: In <b5_0>1922<b5_0/>, <a0_0><b8_0>Benito Mussolini<b8_0/>'s<a0_0/> rise to power in Italy brought profound changes to the colonial government in Italian Eritrea. <a1_0>After il Duce declared the birth of the Italian Empire<a1_0/> in <a2_0>May <b7_0>1936<b7_0/><a2_0/>, Italian Eritrea (enlarged with northern Ethiopia's regions) and Italian Somaliland were merged with the just conquered Ethiopia in the new <a4_0>Italian East Africa<a4_0/> (Africa Orientale Italiana) administrative territory. This Fascist period was characterized by imperial expansion in the name of a "new Roman Empire". <b6_0>Eritrea<b6_0/> was chosen by the Italian government to be the <a3_0>industrial center of Italian East Africa<a3_0/>.
